Metricbeat and Filebeat sidecars for each ES pod, so I need to figure out the logging situation. Looking at the standard ES Docker image, it should be writing logs to `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/` in addition to stdout, but I'm only seeing gc.log there currently—this could be because the cluster hasn't had enough activity to generate application logs yet.\n\nThe default Docker configuration might only log to console, so I'll need to configure ES to write to files or mount a shared volume for the sidecars to read from. For the Metricbeat sidecar, I'll set up the elasticsearch-xpack module to collect metrics from the local ES instance and ship them to the monitoring cluster. I'll set up a shared volume between the ES and Filebeat containers so Filebeat can read the logs that ES writes to disk, then create ConfigMaps for the logging configuration and monitoring sidecars before patching the StatefulSet to include everything together. Now I need to write out the log4j2 properties file...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":747,"cache_read_input_tokens":34675,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":747},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77ff193e-e364-4989-988e-248143808fa8","uuid":"f5a9fe90-d354-4e89-83c1-b23a234ced77","request_id":"req_011CcfyGFWv1Np2U6Nrmkdar"}
