{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EMMpBPAQVMVbn2PwiEAyNZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's already a `log4j2.file.properties` that configures file-based rolling logging. This is the full file-based logging configuration that ES uses when running non-containerized. I can use this as the log4j2 config for the ES container if I mount it as `log4j2.properties`.\n\nActually wait - the way ES Docker image works:\n- In Docker/container mode, it uses `log4j2.properties` (the one we already saw - Console only)\n- When running as a process (non-Docker), it uses `log4j2.file.properties`\nThe file-based config references `${sys:es.logs.base_path}`, which gets set by the `path.logs` setting in `elasticsearch.yml` and defaults to `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs` in the Docker image. So I can mount the file-based properties as a ConfigMap overlay, which will direct ES to write logs to that directory, then share that same volume with Filebeat to pick them up.\n\nI need to check what the root logger configuration in `log4j2.file.properties` specifies to understand how the cluster name gets included in the log filenames.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":897,"cache_read_input_tokens":44614,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":897},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77ff193e-e364-4989-988e-248143808fa8","uuid":"075a38cf-26e9-422a-92e8-bf9daaf132d1","request_id":"req_011CcfyNWbSa1BH17ruN3Mzc"}
