{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Rpg29PATdaPi9sjWVkrs5g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The server JSON log file looks correct - each line is valid JSON with `{\"type\": \"server\", ...}`. So the Filebeat JSON errors shouldn't be coming from this file.\n\nOh wait - looking at the Filebeat error: `\"json: cannot unmarshal string into Go value of type map[string]interface{}\"`. This is a Go JSON unmarshaling error that occurs when the JSON value is a valid JSON string but not an object. \n\nLooking at the ES server log format: `{\"type\": \"server\", ...}`. Each line is a valid JSON object. So why is Filebeat failing?\nActually, I think I see it now - some log entries with stacktraces span multiple lines. The `ESJsonLayout` produces JSON objects that can break across lines when there's a stacktrace included. Without multiline handling configured in Filebeat, it's treating each line as a separate JSON document, so the second line of a multi-line entry becomes invalid JSON that Filebeat can't parse.\n\nThe simplest solution is to disable JSON parsing in Filebeat entirely since it doesn't actually need to parse the JSON - it can just ship the raw log lines as-is and they'll still be captured in the monitoring system.\n\nUpdating the Filebeat configuration to remove JSON parsing...\n\nThe multiline pattern with `negate: true` and `match: after` will append any lines that don't start with `{` to the previous line, which handles Elasticsearch JSON logs where stacktraces span multiple lines. I'll go with the simplest approach—skip JSON parsing entirely and just configure multiline handling for the ES JSON format.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1165,"cache_read_input_tokens":87166,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1165},"output_tokens":16,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77ff193e-e364-4989-988e-248143808fa8","uuid":"44e3a025-8eb0-4623-997b-15ecbbbd8dc5","request_id":"req_011CcfzDEEob3hes4RhBUfxM"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Rpg29PATdaPi9sjWVkrs5g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The JSON parse errors are from multi-line log entries (stacktraces break across lines). Let me fix Filebeat to use multiline handling instead of JSON parsing:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1165,"cache_read_input_tokens":87166,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1165},"output_tokens":16,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77ff193e-e364-4989-988e-248143808fa8","uuid":"b51119b0-ec4b-4864-a48c-6059bddd466e","request_id":"req_011CcfzDEEob3hes4RhBUfxM"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Rpg29PATdaPi9sjWVkrs5g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0122CSqRVcVyb8Qoo69yspPt","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat <<'EOF' | kubectl apply -f -\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: filebeat-monitoring-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  filebeat.yml: |\n    filebeat.inputs:\n    - type: log\n      enabled: true\n      paths:\n        - /usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/*_server.json\n        - /usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/*.log\n        - /usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/gc.log*\n      multiline.pattern: '^{'\n      multiline.negate: true\n      multiline.match: after\n      fields:\n        log_type: elasticsearch\n        cluster_name: es-cluster\n      fields_under_root: false\n\n    output.elasticsearch:\n      hosts: [\"http://monitoring-es-http.monitoring.svc.cluster.local:9200\"]\n      index: \"monitoring-es-logs-%{+yyyy.MM.dd}\"\n\n    setup.template.name: \"monitoring-es-logs\"\n    setup.template.pattern: \"monitoring-es-logs-*\"\n    setup.ilm.enabled: false\n\n    monitoring.enabled: false\n    logging.level: info\n    logging.to_files: false\nEOF","description":"Update Filebeat config with multiline handling, no JSON parsing"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1165,"cache_read_input_tokens":87166,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1165},"output_tokens":16,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77ff193e-e364-4989-988e-248143808fa8","uuid":"722dd157-910a-4dab-9b57-a84574ab4335","request_id":"req_011CcfzDEEob3hes4RhBUfxM"}
